text:

Notable equipment:
- 2 x half racks
- 3 x full racks with attached platforms
- Plate loaded leg press
- Glute drive machine
- V squat machine
- T bar row
- Lateral raise machine
- Many pulldown machines (front pulldown, isolateral wide pulldown, regular pulldown, diverging lat pulldown)

author: Justin
text:
the one true AF deserving of the tampines title. from L1 it looks really unassuming and seeing that it has been opened for quite awhile, one would think that the equipment would be rusty and some equipment faulty. however, stepping into this AF totally blew my mind, 3 rogue power bars + 3 deadlift platforms + 2 squat racks + 1 smith machine impressed me and made me justify the reason why I pay for premium fee for AF. i would rate the gym 4.5/5 stars.

the 0.5 stars room for improvement would be ensure that all equipments are working (only the stairmaster was not working when i visited). an important point to note would be that members are not allowed take off their shirts in the locker area as it is a shared space and sadly there would be no place to take your post-workout pump :( the group classes area is also criminally underutilized even though the mirrors there would be perfect for practicing bodybuilding poses! and this point can be subjectively viewed as either a positive or negative

text:
Unreasonable staff who banned my friends for a lengthy period without adequate reason. While my friends did use chalk, they had cleaned up after themselves all the while whenever they had used it. A staff member had come up to them and informed them they had to leave because of their chalk usage.

My friends did not object, but while they were preparing to leave they were informed that they would be banned for an entire week. In what way is this fair to paying customers?

author: ç™½Kane
text:
This is my honest review coming from a pioneer member that join during the early days (2017) since their last location was at Tampines North Community Centre. I witnessed how it all started off with their first stationed regional manager, Matt and their first in house trainer, Manfred. Then Alice and Safid came aboard with a few very friendly going intern like Berry. (We even had dinner to celebrate his last day before he entered NS). Over the course of years, I have watched both Alice and Safid getting promoted and taking on bigger responsibilities and roles.

The club was very professionally managed by Alice and Safid. I do visit the gym 6 days a week. It was a very friendly gym. Starting from AF staffs greeting you in and out of the gym (Heartwarming pleasant experience =) ). And then came COVID19. The gym had to be closed due to government regulations. The gym did care about their members and was kind enough to even loan out dumbbells and benches to work out at home.

After their shutdown of operation in October 2021 (Due to CC renovation), I tried to work out at other Tampines AF gym. But after two months of traveling, I finally came to decision to cancel this membership as Iâ€™m unable to commit to such traveling. I stopped hitting the gym for 8 months. I was elated to join back the gym in late July 2022.

Today 1st of September 2022, at or around 3pm â€“ 3.30pm, while I was using the chest press machine, I was approached and reprimanded by their trainer, Sheikh by a condescending and rude tone, for slamming the weights. I was shocked and I immediately apologized to him for my negligence and explained to him that I had earbuds with noise cancelations effects, and I was pushing myself hard with one more max rep method. In a rude manner, he refused to accept my explanation and calls me giving excuses. He reprimanded me that I should have let the machine down slowly. I again explained I was pushing myself.

We both had a heated argument. During the argument, he used rude phrase such as â€œYou believe that I can ask you to get out of the gym. Iâ€™m authorized to doâ€, threatening to order me to get out of gym during my workout. During the arguments, I accidentally tap his chest gently which apologized to him immediately it was unintentional but to my disbelief, I witnessed Sheikh responded by raising his fist and said â€œwhy you touch me, touch me again I will punch youâ€. I was even provoked and challenged to go to the manager room to continue this heated argument.

As a paying customer, Iâ€™m shocked to receive such a rude and rough approach from Sheikh. This is my first time that I have been reprimanded with such a harsh tone and barbaric body language and gestures coming from a AF staff. I been training the same way since 2017 with Tampines AF gym. No issues! Not even one verbal warning!

My point of view, as a staff representing AF, an international brand, trainer Sheikh was supposed to behave in a professional behavior in his workplace to be primarily respectful and demonstrate courteous conduct to provide a safe environment for gym goers(customers) to work out.  If Sheikh had took on a more professional approach and demonstrate polite gestures and body languages and accepting my first initial apology and explanation, none of this will have happened!

It was such a depressing awful experience for me as a customer to go through what I went through today. No paying customer should deserve to be treated like this!

From this incident, I deeply regretted to join back this gym considering that other gyms are offering competitive pricing with classes. One of main reason that convinced me to join back was that it is still managed by Safid and Alice. I guess all it took was one black sheep to destroy all the pleasant customer experience they have built from scratch.

author: Chia Feng Yuan
text:
Today was looking forward to my first time visiting Tampines North CC Anytime Fitness outlet. But after reaching, me and my friend were told that we had to wait close to an hour to enter, and that the open slots were reserved for their home members. If we want to wait, we had to tap in using our token and scan the barcode displayed through their glass window.

I was very disappointed by the assistance and the customer service that this outlet displayed.

First of all, is it not that all Customers are able to access any outlets after the 1st month of membership application? So what is the difference between your home members and us? Aren't we all paying the same amount? We are all paying a monthly fee to gain access to the gym facilities and your services, but why should me and my friend get preferential treatment?

Second of all, the customer service is poor. When we were told to tap in using the token, and scan the barcode displayed through their glass window, and that is it. The service providers from this outlet, did not even brief us on what we should do after scanning the barcode. It took me 5 mins just to scan the barcode. After scanning, the barcode leads me to the whatsapp group, which then we do not know how to proceed.

Last of all, the service providers were not even friendly. I had been to 2 other outlets so far, and my experience with them were fantastic. The service providers from those 2 outlets were very friendly and engaging, they are always open for assistance. But i was utterly unhappy with the treatment and the service that the Tampines North CC Anytime Fitness portrayed, ruining my experience and the excitement of visiting a new outlet.

author: Alex Cheong
text:
The friendliest Anytime Fitness Branch around..

Club took initiative to prioritise entry for home club members which is GEATLY appreciated in such times where there is limitation to total personnel allowed to work out In the gym at one time.

There is almost zero to none waiting time for home clubbers during peak hours and kudos to the all the staffs for the perfect club culture and overall atmosphere and environment of the gym!

From club manager Alice, PT Safid, BA Herdy, intern Barry and the new trainer on board, Love you guys!

Thanks for making my daily go to place after work so enjoyable!

text:
Gym closed since Oct 2021.. 4 months now and counting - members stuck paying fees or forced to go farther location.
They sent email that Tampines North will closed for relocation starting 30th Sept. Supposed to Open in December.. it is already CNY 2022 and gym still no update. They don't care, members account are being deducted payment anyway.  They are just ripping members off to go to farther location or pay full monthly fee for nothing. All the lockdowns in  2020 and 2021, this gym didn't bother to get new location?? now members how to suffer due to management incompetence and laziness! completely unprofessional and rip off. Go sign elsewhere.. location is 1 of the main reason for choosing gym, why force members???

text:

This Anytime Fitness gym is a lot smaller, but is filled with a wide variety of equipment for a solid workout. It gets packed towards the evening, and is very empty before 7am.

Has 3 changing rooms with shower facilities, a water cooler, open racks for bag placement, and a small waiting lounge.
